Before examining CEO salaries in large companies, it's important to establish a clear definition of what constitutes a large company. Generally, large companies are characterized by:

-   Having more than 500 employees
-   Annual revenue exceeding \$1 billion

Please note that these criteria may vary depending on the industry or region. For a more detailed understanding of how large businesses are defined, you can refer to the [SBA's Size Standards](https://www.sba.gov/federal-contracting/contracting-guide/size-standards).

